{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"a9fbbbe5896b1a951","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a correctness-bug finder reviewing an uncommitted working-tree diff in c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test (run `git diff HEAD` there; `git status --short` for new untracked files). Review scope: the data-path and state-changing logic of the metric-quotas feature.\n\nAngle: CROSS-FILE TRACER. For each changed function (quotas_repo.read_tenant_quota_state_locked, quotas_repo.upsert_quota, events_service.create_event, quota_service functions, api_key.verify_api_key with the new scope field, errors.AppError handling), Grep for its callers and check whether the change breaks any call site: new preconditions, changed return shapes, new exceptions escaping to the wrong layer, lock/transaction ordering dependencies between quotas_repo and events_repo (deadlock potential: do all code paths acquire the quota-row lock and rollup-row upsert in the same order?), and RLS/tenant-key consistency (does the quota check read usage_rollup under the same api_key_id the events write path uses?). Also check the migration's constraints match what the repo code assumes (scope CHECK values, quotas PK, CHECK limit>=1).\n\nReturn up to 6 candidate findings, each as: file, line, one-line summary, concrete failure_scenario. Only candidates with a nameable failure scenario. If none, say none."},"uuid":"ac9669e1-063d-4bce-a628-bfb4e084a1f9","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:03:52.829Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
